reviews.text: We love so much about these, but the biggest issues are around the fact that they prevent most switch plate covers from laying flat. All this has to do with the thickness of the tabs and the fact that they a portion you must awkwardly snap off. Plastic on the tabs also can interfere with easy screw tightening. the irony is the engineers intentions were probably good....trying to make larger tabs that interlock for fixed spacing and flatter installations, but this was a big fail. the tabs are bigger but too flimsy to force outlets flat and the problems above were created. The auto spacing kinda works. The actual outlet and switch features are great. Easy to install wires and no exposed wires or contacts. Please make tabs out of all metal

reviews.text: These things are just too cool. I've always had good luck with the Leviton brand. If you joined a switch with a Wago connector, this is what you would get. This greatly simplifies installation. No more bending j-hooks. Just: Strip the wire, flip open the lever, push the wire into the hole, flip the lever closed, and give the wire a little tug to insure it's secured. It couldn't be easier. If you're doing any remodeling, make sure to get some of the Leviton wall receptacles with this same feature. You will thank yourself. I would definitely recommend this item.

reviews.text: I'm upgrading all of my light switches to Kasa Smart Switches but not every switch needs to be smart, especially on 3-way and 4-way circuits. I originally started with some cheap rocker switches but returned them when I found the Decora Edge. Smart switches take up a lot of space in multi-gang boxes, which doesn't leave much room for wire nuts or Wago connectors. With these switches, the wires stab directly into the switch or outlet and are much safer vs. backstabbing, which every YouTube electrician and DIYer says not to do. One warning, these switches are huge and you'll want to make sure your wallplate is going to fit.

reviews.title: Save space in your switch box and cut your installation time in half with the Decor Edge Switches

reviews.text: I am replacing all my toggle switches with these and I know folks will say to only use screw terminals, but these really are great. While one usually has to strip the wire when switching switches, not having to bend the wire place it around the screw (in the correct direction) really does save a lot of time. Folks I am sure will say a screw terminal is tighter and more secure, but I really pulled on these after pushing down the lever…didn’t you move at all. I trust the brand so that is why I went with this style (wouldn’t for a random brand).
